# Block Development Workflow

## Critical Rule: Always Update Three JSON Files

**Whenever you create a new block or modify an existing block, you MUST update these three files:**

1. **component-definition.json** - Register the block definition
2. **component-filters.json** - Add block to section components (if applicable) and create filter (if block has child components)
3. **component-models.json** - Define the block's model with all fields

## Workflow Checklist

### When Creating a New Block:

1. ✅ Create block files:
   - `blocks/[block-name]/[block-name].js`
   - `blocks/[block-name]/[block-name].css`
   - `blocks/[block-name]/_[block-name].json`

2. ✅ Update `component-definition.json`:
   - Add block definition to appropriate group (usually "Blocks")
   - Include proper resourceType, template name, model/filter references

3. ✅ Update `component-filters.json`:
   - Add block ID to `"section"` components array (so it can be added to sections)
   - If block has child components, create a new filter entry with `"id": "[block-name]"` and `"components": [...]`

4. ✅ Update `component-models.json`:
   - Add model definition with `"id": "[block-name]"`
   - Define all fields with proper component types (text, richtext, reference, select, boolean, container, etc.)
   - Include field labels, descriptions, options (for select), validation (if needed)

5. ✅ Verify JSON validity:
   - Run `npm run build:json` to regenerate merged files
   - Check for JSON syntax errors
   - Validate all references are correct

## Pattern Guidelines

### Use "model" for:
- Blocks with structured data fields
- Example: `"model": "teaser"`

### Use "filter" for:
- Blocks that contain child components
- Example: `"filter": "tabs"` (tabs contain tabs-item components)

### Use both "model" and "filter" for:
- Blocks that have both structured data AND child components
- Example: `"model": "tabs", "filter": "tabs"`

### Use "key-value": true for:
- Blocks that use key-value pair configuration
- Example: Teaser block

## Field Types Reference

- `"component": "text"` - Simple text input
- `"component": "richtext"` - Rich text editor
- `"component": "reference"` - Asset reference (images, etc.)
- `"component": "select"` - Dropdown with options
- `"component": "boolean"` - True/false checkbox
- `"component": "container"` - Grouped fields
- `"component": "aem-content"` - AEM content path picker
- `"component": "custom-asset-namespace:custom-asset"` - Custom asset picker (Dynamic Media)

## Example: Complete Block Registration

### 1. Block JSON (`blocks/my-block/_my-block.json`):
```json
{
  "definitions": [
    {
      "title": "My Block",
      "id": "my-block",
      "plugins": {
        "xwalk": {
          "page": {
            "resourceType": "core/franklin/components/block/v1/block",
            "template": {
              "name": "My Block",
              "model": "my-block"
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "models": [
    {
      "id": "my-block",
      "fields": [
        {
          "component": "text",
          "name": "title",
          "label": "Title",
          "valueType": "string"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
  "filters": []
}
```

### 2. component-definition.json:
Add to "Blocks" group:
```json
{
  "title": "My Block",
  "id": "my-block",
  "plugins": {
    "xwalk": {
      "page": {
        "resourceType": "core/franklin/components/block/v1/block",
        "template": {
          "name": "My Block",
          "model": "my-block"
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

### 3. component-filters.json:
Add to section components:
```json
{
  "id": "section",
  "components": [
    ...existing components...,
    "my-block"
  ]
}
```

### 4. component-models.json:
Add model definition:
```json
{
  "id": "my-block",
  "fields": [
    {
      "component": "text",
      "name": "title",
      "label": "Title",
      "valueType": "string"
    }
  ]
}
```

## Verification Steps

After making changes:

1. ✅ Run `npm run build:json` to regenerate merged files
2. ✅ Validate JSON: `node -e "JSON.parse(require('fs').readFileSync('component-definition.json', 'utf8'))"`
3. ✅ Check Universal Editor - block should appear in palette
4. ✅ Test block functionality - all fields should be editable
5. ✅ Verify no console errors

## Common Mistakes to Avoid

❌ **Don't forget** to add block to `component-filters.json` section components
❌ **Don't forget** to create model in `component-models.json`
❌ **Don't forget** to add filter entry if block has child components
❌ **Don't forget** to run `npm run build:json` after changes
❌ **Don't forget** to validate JSON syntax

## Remember

**Every block MUST be registered in all three files for it to work properly in Universal Editor!**
